        // Test cases
        System.out.println(isPowerOfThree(27)); // Should output true
        System.out.println(isPowerOfThree(0));  // Should output false
        System.out.println(isPowerOfThree(-1)); // Should output false
    }
}
```

This solution is more straightforward and avoids any potential issues with floating-point precision. It works because if `n` is a power of three, it must evenly divide the maximum power of three that fits in the integer range. This approach is valid only because the problem constrains the input to a specific range.

